{# EXAMPLE: Open-Ended Radiological Captioning #}
{# Supports single image or multi-image captioning. #}
{# Requires at least one image. #}

**TASK:**

{% if images and images|length > 1 %}
Provide a comprehensive radiological description of these images, as would appear in a formal radiology report.
{% else %}
Provide a comprehensive radiological description of this image, as would appear in a formal radiology report.
{% endif %}

Your caption should include:
1. Technique (modality, sequence, plane if identifiable)
2. Systematic description of visible structures
3. Any abnormal findings with precise descriptions
4. Overall impression

{% if clinical_history %}
**CLINICAL HISTORY:** {{ clinical_history }}
{% endif %}

{% if images and images|length > 0 %}
**IMAGES:**
{% for img in images %}
- {% if img.label %}{{ img.label }}{% else %}Image {{ loop.index }}{% endif %}: {{ img.width }}x{{ img.height }}
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

**OUTPUT FORMAT:**

```json
{
{% if images and images|length > 1 %}
  "images": [
    {
      "image_index": 0,
      "image_label": "string",
      "technique": "string (imaging modality and parameters)",
      "findings": "string (description of this specific image)"
    }
  ],
  "comparative_findings": "string (findings spanning multiple images)",
{% else %}
  "technique": "string (imaging modality and parameters)",
{% endif %}
  "findings": {
    "normal_structures": "string (systematic description of normal anatomy)",
    "abnormalities": "string (detailed description of any pathology)",
    "incidental_findings": "string (any additional observations)"
  },
  "impression": "string (summary statement of key findings)",
  "caption": "string (complete radiological caption suitable for publication)",
  "continue": true/false
}
```

**CAPTIONING GUIDELINES:**

- Use standard radiological terminology
- Be systematic: describe structures in consistent anatomical order
- Quantify findings when possible (size, number, location)
- Describe morphology: shape, margins, signal/density characteristics
- Note relationships to adjacent structures
- State explicitly if an area is normal or unremarkable
- The "caption" field should be a single flowing paragraph suitable for publication
{% if images and images|length > 1 %}
- When describing multiple images, note which findings appear in which image
- Describe any changes or differences between images
{% endif %}
